name: pipeline construction, natural gas, high pressure distribution network | pipeline, natural gas, high pressure distribution network | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/2181/documentation

Pipeline infrastructure for gas distribution in the high and middle pressure distribution network. Life time 40 years. Annual transport of  19 TJ/km/a. 6'380 km pipelines (about 2'000 km steel, 4'000 km PE, 400 km cast iron).;Material requirements of the pipeline system are round 20t/km steel, 0.7 t/km cast iron, 3t/km PE, 0.6 t/km bitumes, 800t/km sand, 4t/km cement. These values are calculated based on the material density, the thickness of the pipeline wall and the kilometers of the various pipeline types.



This dataset describes the infrastructure needed for the Swiss high (>1 bar) and middle (>0.1 bar) pressure distribution network.
category: F:Construction/42:Civil engineering/422:Construction of utility projects/4220:Construction of utility projects

processDocumentation.geographyDescription: Data is based on Swiss data.
processDocumentation.technologyDescription: The length of the pipelines is based on statistics, whereas the thickness of the pipeline is estimated.
